Installing :
1) - install the source in /opt_src/Jiny-Kernel/....
2) - install the lwip source from /opt_src/Jiny-Kernel/util/lwip.tar.gz in to /opt_src/lwip/
 -------------------------
 Compiling Source Code:
 cd /opt_src/Jiny-Kernel
 ./build_g2image      
 ----------------------------
1)  virtio+net:
   ./qemu-system-x86_64 -gdb tcp::1236 -m 1024M -hda /opt_src/Jiny-Kernel/bin/g2_bootdisk -hdb /opt_src/Jiny-Kernel/bin/g2_image -enable-kvm   -vnc :7 -netdev tap,id=guest0,vhost=on,vhostforce -smp 2 -device virtio-net-pci,mac=00:30:48:DB:5E:06,netdev=guest0 -serial telnet::50008,server,nowait -fsdev local,security_model=passthrough,id=fsdev0,path=/opt_src/Jiny-Kernel/test/root/ -device virtio-9p-pci,id=fs0,fsdev=fsdev0,mount_tag=hostshare -monitor tcp::51008,server,nowait,nodelay
   test client:
     test/udp_test/a.out 10.209.129.123 1024 200000
   
 2) virtio+p9:
    ./qemu-system-x86_64 -s -m 1024M -hda /opt_src/Jiny-Kernel/bin/g2_bootdisk -hdb /opt_src/Jiny-Kernel/bin/g2_image -enable-kvm   -vnc :4 -fsdev local,security_model=passthrough,id=fsdev0,path=/home/jana -device virtio-9p-pci,id=fs0,fsdev=fsdev0,mount_tag=hostshare   
     
     Testing P9:
        cat test_file
------------------------------
Constructing the image for grub2 (Not sucessfull):

dd if=/dev/zero of=bin/g2_image bs=512 count=8000
--sudo losetup /dev/loop0 -d
--sudo losetup /dev/loop0  bin/g2_image
--sudo mke2fs /dev/loop0
mke2fs bin/g2_image
sudo mount /dev/loop0 /tmp/ab/
populate files into /tmp/ab/


sudo umount /tmp/ab
sudo grub-install --force  /dev/loop0 
-------------------------------
WorkAround:
    - use old image as bootable disk for grub, use second disk to store the kernel.
-----------------------------------
Running on KVM:

./ivshmem_server -m 2m -p /tmp/jana
sudo ./qemu-system-x86_64 -s -m 1024M -L /home/njana/qemu/opt/qemu.12.5/share/qemu -hda /home/njana/jiny/bin/g2_bootdisk -hdb /home/njana/jiny/bin/g2_image -enable-kvm  -chardev socket,path=/tmp/jana,id=jana -device ivshmem,chardev=jana,size=2m,msi=off -serial /dev/pts/1 -vnc :4
 
serial :
  -serial /dev/pt/1 
where /dev/pts/1 is the pty for the console running qemu

Attaching to gdb: (add -S to qemu command line)
 
target remote localhost:1234 
set architecture i386:x86-64
---------------------------------------------------
Running on Xen:

xl create -c ./jiny_xen.conf
gdbsx -a 1 64  9999

-----------------------------------
git push may give error, in that case changes the url in .git/config as : url = git@github.com:naredula-jana/Jiny-Kernel.git
-------------------------------------

